catFacts.name: Siamese
catFacts.fact: Siamese cats are one of the oldest and most recognizable breeds in the world.

catFacts.name: Bombay
catFacts.fact: Bombay cats are often called 'mini panthers' because of their sleek black coats and gold eyes.

catFacts.name: Maine Coon
catFacts.fact: Maine Coon cats are one of the largest domesticated cat breeds, known for their tufted ears and bushy tails.

catFacts.name: British Shorthair
catFacts.fact: British Shorthair cats are known for their stocky build, dense coat, and round face.

catFacts.name: Sphynx
catFacts.fact: Sphynx cats are known for their lack of fur and affectionate nature.

catFacts.name: Egyptian Mau
catFacts.fact: Egyptian Maus are one of the few naturally spotted breeds of domesticated cat.
